  "about": {
    "contact_email": "You can contact us via email",
    "description": {
      "title": "Roj Ava Center for Strategic Studies is an independent, non-profit political and intellectual foundation established based on contemporary historical and strategic necessities",
      "paragraph1": "Through its work, outputs, and writings, it seeks to positively influence the trajectory of historical developments in the political geography of Kurdish societies in general, and Roj Ava and Syria in particular, by presenting topics, proposals, analyses, studies, surveys, and multiple ideas, organizing international and local seminars, and strategic meetings between political and intellectual elites in the Middle East and the world, aiming to build a democratic Kurdish and Middle Eastern society based on the values of justice and equality, through the approach of \"democratic nation\" that calls for respecting the specificities of all societies, nationalities, religions, and sects, without gender discrimination, respecting women, and advocating for full partnership in rights and duties. The center also believes in and works to preserve the environment and human and ecological history by spreading an environmental culture aimed at preserving the civilizational heritage of all human societies.",
      "paragraph2": "Hence, the Roj Ava Center for Strategic Studies website develops its diverse follow-ups and research, investing them in formulating strategic future proposals and visions that contribute to raising the level of awareness and critical sense of individuals and society.",
      "paragraph3": "The website is committed to publishing professional studies, analyses, and journalistic materials, provided that their content contributes to reaching and moving towards facts away from all forms of oppression, exclusion, and intolerance in all their forms."
    }
  },
